Returns: The requested @B_com#google#android#gms#games#multiplayer#turnbased#TurnBasedMatch_E@ object. Note that this may be null, depending on the status code returned.

ClassDesc: Result delivered when a turn-based match has been loaded. Possible status codes include: @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_OK_E@ if data was successfully loaded and is up-to-date. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_NETWORK_ERROR_NO_DATA_E@ if the device was unable to retrieve any data from the network and has no data cached locally. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_NETWORK_ERROR_STALE_DATA_E@ if the device was unable to retrieve the latest data from the network, but has some data cached locally. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_MATCH_NOT_FOUND_E@ if the requested match does not exist on the server. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_CLIENT_RECONNECT_REQUIRED_E@ if the client needs to reconnect to the service to access this data. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR_E@ if an unexpected error occurred in the service.
